I attended the 2nd Gymnasium till 6th grade, after which I immigrated to the United States. I was in 6b class. Many of you might also remember my mother, Alexandra Iakovlena Shats,  she was the Art teacher and later became the homeroom  teacher for 6A. I currently live in Brooklyn, NY and attend LIU University Pharmacy School. I am very happy to find many of my old classmates and friends here, and am really interested in reestablishing communication with many. Also I want to catch up on what I missed in the past 7 years through stories and pictures, so any help is welcome. I am still fluent in Russian, but it is easier for me to type in English since I dont have a Russian keyboard on my laptop.  I think that's it for now =c]
